      "date": "2018-09-20 15:23:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nDoes this really solve the problem, or will later OSCs in the list not be handled very often?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "653e99f68a1720806b88e47daba49aac808e6562",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2018-09-20 16:07:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nevery time it scans all the OSCs registered and finds the closest (in terms of time) OSC, then it will schedule next work for that time. recently processed OSCs won't be processed because they haven't expired yet, so they won't be accounted for rpc_sent.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "72ff497e2a4598b3735eb37c1dba36a5e2b9866c",
