      },
      "date": "2018-10-16 08:07:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n>  What if there are 300 OSCs?  Then the first 100 will be processed, then the second 100 will be processed on the next call, but will the first 100 timeout before we get to the 300th or 1000th or 2000th OSC?\n\nosc_grant_work_handler() walks through all OSCs and schedules to process the closest one. so if some \"far-on-list\" OSC should schedule this work as soon as possible, essentially \"now\". given default 20min shrink interval, I think the case you describe is unlikely.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
